transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Viagra, can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I want to cancel my subscription because it said $49 and what?

Speaker 1: I can take a look into your profile. What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 2: Russell 726, 76273.

Speaker 1: Okay, I pulled it up here. So yeah, you bought our Viagra AGV. $49 is the medication.

Speaker 2: There's a $14 pharmacy fee to dispense it. Total is $63 for the 10 pills that are AGV.

Speaker 1: Oh, okay. Is this – I don't want it like every 30 days. I just want to try it and then –

Speaker 2: Yeah, so the way it works is the prescription, since it's through Pfizer,

Speaker 1: it needs a refill date to become active.

Speaker 2: It doesn't mean you need to take the second order. It just needs the refill date.

Speaker 1: That way they can ship out your first order.

Speaker 2: What I could do for you, though, is freeze out any future orders to give you an opportunity to try it

Speaker 1: and see if you even like it. Then call us back as soon as you try it so that we can make a final choice.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, I want to do that.

Speaker 1: Sure, just reach out to us. Other than that, you're all set and your order will ship out tomorrow

Speaker 2: to arrive in three to five business days.

Speaker 1: And there won't be no more after that until I call you back, right?

Speaker 2: Exactly, yeah. Just reach out to us after that to confirm if you want to continue or not.

Speaker 1: Okay, all right. I appreciate it.

Speaker 2: No problem. Have a good day. Bye-bye.

Speaker 1: You too.
